cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel method for robot-to-human communication using motion, specifically for underwater robots. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on the design of nonverbal robot-to-human communication methods and evaluates their effectiveness through a user study. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper may involve computer vision techniques for detecting and interpreting the robot's motion. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper may involve machine learning or other AI techniques for recognizing and generating the robot's body language gestures. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper may involve control systems for the robot's motion and communication.
